      <div class = "container m-5">
         
          <h1> Wordle Project </h1>
        <p> <b>Rules:</b> Guess the five letter word. After submitting a guess, the characters will be color coded as below. </p>
        <ul>
          <li id = "rule1">The Letter is in The <span class = "correct"> CORRECT  Position </span> </li>
          <li id = "rule2">The Letter is in The <span class = "wrong"> WRONG Position</span></li>
          <li id = "rule3">The Letter is <span class = "not">NOT in The Word</span></li>
        </ul>
<p>Guesses do not need to be real words, but need to be five letters. For more fun, go to <a class = "wordle" href="https://www.nytimes.com/games/wordle/index.html">Wordle</a></p>
 

        
        
        <form onsubmit = "return false;">
  <input type="text" id="Letter0"  maxlength="1" style="text-transform:uppercase">
